---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<BaseLayout title="Our Programmes — A Worthy | Primary, Secondary & JC Tuition in Singapore" description="Explore A Worthy's comprehensive tuition programmes for Primary (P3-P6), Secondary (Sec 1-4/5), and JC students in Singapore. Mathematics, Science, English & more.">
  <Header slot="header" />

  <!-- ===== PAGE HERO ===== -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-content animate-fade-in-up">
        <span class="hero-badge">Structured Learning for Every Level</span>
        <h1>Our <span class="highlight">Programmes</span></h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">
          From Primary 3 to JC2, our MOE-aligned programmes are designed to build deep understanding,
          sharpen exam technique, and help every student achieve their personal best.
        </p>
        <nav class="programme-nav" aria-label="Programme quick links">
          <a href="#primary" class="nav-pill">Primary</a>
          <a href="#secondary" class="nav-pill">Secondary</a>
          <a href="#jc" class="nav-pill">JC</a>
          <a href="#enrichment" class="nav-pill">Enrichment</a>
          <a href="#holiday" class="nav-pill">Holiday Intensives</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== PRIMARY PROGRAMME ===== -->
  <section class="section programme-section" id="primary">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="level-tag">Primary</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Primary Programme (P3 &ndash; P6)</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">Build strong foundations and PSLE confidence through hands-on, concept-driven learning.</p>
      </div>

      <img src="/images/programmes/primary-students.jpg" alt="Primary students in class" class="programme-section-img" loading="lazy" />

      <div class="subjects-grid">
        <!-- Mathematics -->
        <div class="card subject-card">
          <div class="subject-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 2l20 20"/><path d="M2 2v16l4-4"/><path d="M2 2h16l-4 4"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Mathematics</h3>
          <p>Master problem-solving from the ground up with structured approaches tailored to the PSLE format.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>Model drawing & heuristics</li>
            <li>Problem sums (before/after, assumption, working backwards)</li>
            <li>Whole numbers, fractions & decimals</li>
            <li>Ratios & percentages</li>
            <li>Geometry & mensuration</li>
            <li>Data analysis & interpretation</li>
            <li>PSLE format practice & timed drills</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Science -->
        <div class="card subject-card">
          <div class="subject-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M9 3h6v7l4 8H5l4-8V3z"/><path d="M9 3h6"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Science</h3>
          <p>Develop scientific reasoning and process skills through inquiry-based learning and structured answering techniques.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>Process skills (comparing, classifying, inferring, predicting)</li>
            <li>Open-ended question techniques (CER method)</li>
            <li>Experimental design & variables</li>
            <li>Diversity of living & non-living things</li>
            <li>Cycles in plants & animals</li>
            <li>Systems (human body, plant, electrical)</li>
            <li>Interactions (forces, ecosystems)</li>
            <li>Energy (forms, conversion, heat)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- English -->
        <div class="card subject-card">
          <div class="subject-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 20h9"/><path d="M16.5 3.5a2.121 2.121 0 013 3L7 19l-4 1 1-4L16.5 3.5z"/></svg></div>
          <h3>English Language</h3>
          <p>Strengthen all four language pillars &mdash; reading, writing, listening, and speaking &mdash; for holistic English mastery.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>Comprehension: literal, inferential & applied questions</li>
            <li>Composition writing using the STAR method (Setting, Trigger, Action, Result)</li>
            <li>Grammar cloze & sentence synthesis</li>
            <li>Vocabulary enrichment & contextual usage</li>
            <li>Oral communication & stimulus-based conversation</li>
            <li>Listening comprehension practice</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Higher Chinese -->
        <div class="card subject-card subject-card--compact">
          <div class="subject-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><path d="M12 8v8"/><path d="M8 12h8"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Higher Chinese</h3>
          <p>Available for P5 &ndash; P6 students preparing for PSLE Higher Chinese. Focus on comprehension, composition, and oral examination skills.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="programme-meta">
        <div class="meta-item">
          <span class="meta-label">Schedule</span>
          <span class="meta-value">1.5 hours per subject per week</span>
        </div>
        <div class="meta-item">
          <span class="meta-label">Class Size</span>
          <span class="meta-value">Maximum 8 students</span>
        </div>
        <div class="meta-item">
          <span class="meta-label">Fees</span>
          <span class="meta-value fees">$240 &ndash; $320 / month <span class="fee-note">(depending on level)</span></span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SECONDARY PROGRAMME ===== -->
  <section class="section programme-section alt-bg" id="secondary">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="level-tag">Secondary</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Secondary Programme (Sec 1 &ndash; 4/5)</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">Structured revision, exam techniques, and consistent practice for O-Level and N-Level success.</p>
      </div>

      <img src="/images/programmes/secondary-students.jpg" alt="Secondary students learning" class="programme-section-img" loading="lazy" />

      <div class="subjects-grid">
        <!-- E Math & A Math -->
        <div class="card subject-card">
          <div class="subject-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M18 20V10"/><path d="M12 20V4"/><path d="M6 20v-6"/></svg></div>
          <h3>E Math &amp; A Math</h3>
          <p>From Elementary to Additional Mathematics, we cover the full O-Level and N-Level syllabus with rigour and clarity.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>Algebra: equations, inequalities, functions</li>
            <li>Geometry: congruence, similarity, properties of circles</li>
            <li>Trigonometry: ratios, identities, graphs, R-formula</li>
            <li>Calculus: differentiation & integration (A Math)</li>
            <li>Statistics & probability</li>
            <li>GCE O-Level & N-Level paper practice</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sciences -->
        <div class="card subject-card">
          <div class="subject-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M9 3h6v7l4 8H5l4-8V3z"/><path d="M9 3h6"/><circle cx="13" cy="15" r="1"/><circle cx="10" cy="17" r="1"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Pure &amp; Combined Sciences</h3>
          <p>Comprehensive coverage of Physics, Chemistry, and Biology for both Pure and Combined Science tracks.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li><strong>Physics:</strong> mechanics, thermal physics, waves, electricity & magnetism</li>
            <li><strong>Chemistry:</strong> atomic structure, chemical bonding, acids/bases, organic chemistry</li>
            <li><strong>Biology:</strong> cell biology, nutrition, transport, homeostasis, inheritance</li>
            <li>Practical lab skills & SPA preparation</li>
            <li>Structured & free-response question techniques</li>
            <li>Data-based question strategies</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- English -->
        <div class="card subject-card">
          <div class="subject-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 3h6a4 4 0 014 4v14a3 3 0 00-3-3H2z"/><path d="M22 3h-6a4 4 0 00-4 4v14a3 3 0 013-3h7z"/></svg></div>
          <h3>English Language</h3>
          <p>Develop strong comprehension and writing skills to excel across all components of the GCE O-Level English paper.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>Comprehension: inference, language use, summary writing</li>
            <li>Summary writing techniques & paraphrasing skills</li>
            <li>Situational writing (formal & informal)</li>
            <li>Continuous writing: narrative, argumentative, expository</li>
            <li>Visual text comprehension</li>
            <li>Editing & grammar accuracy</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="programme-meta">
        <div class="meta-item">
          <span class="meta-label">Schedule</span>
          <span class="meta-value">2 hours per subject per week</span>
        </div>
        <div class="meta-item">
          <span class="meta-label">Class Size</span>
          <span class="meta-value">Maximum 8 students</span>
        </div>
        <div class="meta-item">
          <span class="meta-label">Fees</span>
          <span class="meta-value fees">$280 &ndash; $380 / month</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== JC PROGRAMME ===== -->
  <section class="section programme-section" id="jc">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="level-tag">Junior College</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">JC Programme (JC1 &ndash; JC2)</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">Rigorous content mastery and exam strategy for the GCE A-Level examinations.</p>
      </div>

      <img src="/images/programmes/jc-students.jpg" alt="JC students studying" class="programme-section-img" loading="lazy" />

      <div class="subjects-grid">
        <!-- H2 Mathematics -->
        <div class="card subject-card">
          <div class="subject-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/></svg></div>
          <h3>H2 Mathematics</h3>
          <p>Deep mastery of both Pure Mathematics and Statistics for H2 Maths, with extensive past-year paper drills.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>Functions & graphs</li>
            <li>Sequences & series (AP, GP, method of differences)</li>
            <li>Vectors in 2D and 3D</li>
            <li>Complex numbers</li>
            <li>Calculus: techniques of differentiation & integration, applications</li>
            <li>Statistics & probability distributions</li>
            <li>Hypothesis testing & regression</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- H2 Physics -->
        <div class="card subject-card">
          <div class="subject-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><polygon points="13 2 3 14 12 14 11 22 21 10 12 10 13 2"/></svg></div>
          <h3>H2 Physics</h3>
          <p>From classical mechanics to modern physics, develop conceptual clarity and problem-solving rigour for the A-Level.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>Mechanics: kinematics, dynamics, energy, momentum</li>
            <li>Waves: superposition, diffraction, interference</li>
            <li>Electricity: circuits, electric & magnetic fields, electromagnetic induction</li>
            <li>Modern physics: quantum theory, nuclear physics</li>
            <li>Practical skills & planning questions</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- H2 Chemistry -->
        <div class="card subject-card">
          <div class="subject-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M9 3h6v7l4 8a2 2 0 01-2 3H7a2 2 0 01-2-3l4-8V3z"/></svg></div>
          <h3>H2 Chemistry</h3>
          <p>Systematic coverage of physical, inorganic, and organic chemistry with emphasis on application and data analysis.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>Atomic structure & chemical bonding</li>
            <li>Chemical energetics & thermodynamics</li>
            <li>Reaction kinetics & equilibria</li>
            <li>Organic chemistry: mechanisms, synthesis, analysis</li>
            <li>Transition metals & electrochemistry</li>
            <li>Practical & planning question techniques</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- H1 General Paper -->
        <div class="card subject-card">
          <div class="subject-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 3h6a4 4 0 014 4v14a3 3 0 00-3-3H2z"/><path d="M22 3h-6a4 4 0 00-4 4v14a3 3 0 013-3h7z"/></svg></div>
          <h3>H1 General Paper</h3>
          <p>Build critical thinking, argumentation, and comprehension skills for confident GP performance.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>Essay writing: structure, argumentation, evaluation</li>
            <li>Comprehension: summary, application, inference</li>
            <li>Current affairs: Singapore & global issues</li>
            <li>Content mastery across key themes (science & tech, media, environment, politics)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- H2 Economics -->
        <div class="card subject-card">
          <div class="subject-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><line x1="12" y1="1" x2="12" y2="23"/><path d="M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 000 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 010 7H6"/></svg></div>
          <h3>H2 Economics</h3>
          <p>Master both micro and macro economics with rigorous case study and essay preparation.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>Microeconomics: demand & supply, market failure, government intervention</li>
            <li>Macroeconomics: national income, inflation, unemployment, trade</li>
            <li>Case study skills: data interpretation, analysis, evaluation</li>
            <li>Essay planning & structuring techniques</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="programme-meta">
        <div class="meta-item">
          <span class="meta-label">Schedule</span>
          <span class="meta-value">2 hours per subject per week</span>
        </div>
        <div class="meta-item">
          <span class="meta-label">Class Size</span>
          <span class="meta-value">Maximum 6 students</span>
        </div>
        <div class="meta-item">
          <span class="meta-label">Fees</span>
          <span class="meta-value fees">$360 &ndash; $450 / month</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== ENRICHMENT PROGRAMMES ===== -->
  <section class="section programme-section alt-bg" id="enrichment">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="level-tag">Enrichment</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Enrichment Programmes</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">Go beyond the syllabus with programmes that develop higher-order thinking and competitive edge.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="enrichment-grid">
        <div class="card enrichment-card">
          <div class="enrichment-icon"><svg width="44" height="44" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2a7 7 0 017 7c0 2.38-1.19 4.47-3 5.74V17a2 2 0 01-2 2h-4a2 2 0 01-2-2v-2.26C6.19 13.47 5 11.38 5 9a7 7 0 017-7z"/><path d="M10 21h4"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Critical Thinking &amp; Problem Solving</h3>
          <p>Sharpen logical reasoning, analytical skills, and creative problem-solving through structured challenges and real-world scenarios. Suitable for P4 &ndash; Sec 2 students looking to strengthen their thinking toolkit beyond the standard curriculum.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card enrichment-card">
          <div class="enrichment-icon"><svg width="44" height="44" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="6"/><path d="M9 18l-3 4"/><path d="M15 18l3 4"/><path d="M12 14v4"/></svg></div>
          <h3>ICAS &amp; Math Olympiad Preparation</h3>
          <p>Targeted training for students competing in ICAS (International Competitions and Assessments for Schools) and the Singapore Mathematical Olympiad. Covers advanced problem types, number theory, combinatorics, and competition strategies.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card enrichment-card">
          <div class="enrichment-icon"><svg width="44" height="44" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 20h9"/><path d="M16.5 3.5a2.121 2.121 0 013 3L7 19l-4 1 1-4L16.5 3.5z"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Creative Writing Workshop</h3>
          <p>Unleash your child's imagination with guided workshops on storytelling, character development, descriptive writing, and creative composition techniques. Perfect for students who want to elevate their writing from good to outstanding.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== HOLIDAY INTENSIVES ===== -->
  <section class="section programme-section" id="holiday">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="level-tag">Seasonal</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Holiday Intensives</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">Focused crash courses and revision bootcamps during the school holidays to maximise learning when it matters most.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="holiday-grid">
        <div class="card holiday-card">
          <div class="holiday-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="5"/><line x1="12" y1="1" x2="12" y2="3"/><line x1="12" y1="21" x2="12" y2="23"/><line x1="4.22" y1="4.22" x2="5.64" y2="5.64"/><line x1="18.36" y1="18.36" x2="19.78" y2="19.78"/><line x1="1" y1="12" x2="3" y2="12"/><line x1="21" y1="12" x2="23" y2="12"/><line x1="4.22" y1="19.78" x2="5.64" y2="18.36"/><line x1="18.36" y1="5.64" x2="19.78" y2="4.22"/></svg></div>
          <h3>June Intensive Programme</h3>
          <p>Use the mid-year break to close gaps and get ahead. Our June intensives cover key topics from Semester 1 and preview Semester 2 content so students return to school with confidence.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>3-hour daily sessions</li>
            <li>Topic-focused modules</li>
            <li>Available for all levels (P3 &ndash; JC2)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card holiday-card">
          <div class="holiday-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2L8 8h8l-4-6z"/><path d="M6 14h12l-6-6-6 6z"/><path d="M4 20h16l-8-6-8 6z"/><line x1="12" y1="20" x2="12" y2="22"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Nov / Dec Intensive Programme</h3>
          <p>Prepare for the year ahead or revise the entire year's syllabus during the long holidays. Ideal for students moving up to a new level (e.g., P6 to Sec 1, Sec 4 to JC1).</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>3-hour daily sessions</li>
            <li>Bridging & head-start modules</li>
            <li>Full-year syllabus review option</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card holiday-card">
          <div class="holiday-icon"><svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Exam Revision Bootcamps</h3>
          <p>Intensive revision leading up to PSLE, GCE O-Level, and GCE A-Level exams. Drill past-year papers, refine exam technique, and boost confidence under timed conditions.</p>
          <ul class="topic-list">
            <li>PSLE Bootcamp (Sep &ndash; Oct)</li>
            <li>O-Level Bootcamp (Sep &ndash; Oct)</li>
            <li>A-Level Bootcamp (Oct &ndash; Nov)</li>
            <li>Daily 3-hour intensive sessions</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== WEEKLY SCHEDULE ===== -->
  <section class="section schedule-section alt-bg" id="schedule">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Weekly Class Schedule</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Classes run on a regular weekly cycle. Contact us for the latest available slots.</p>

      <div class="schedule-table-wrapper">
        <table class="schedule-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Day</th>
              <th>Time</th>
              <th>Programme</th>
              <th>Subjects</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Day">Monday</td>
              <td data-label="Time">4:00 PM &ndash; 5:30 PM</td>
              <td data-label="Programme">Primary (P3 &ndash; P4)</td>
              <td data-label="Subjects">Mathematics, English</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Day">Monday</td>
              <td data-label="Time">6:00 PM &ndash; 8:00 PM</td>
              <td data-label="Programme">Secondary (Sec 1 &ndash; 2)</td>
              <td data-label="Subjects">E Math, Science</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Day">Tuesday</td>
              <td data-label="Time">4:00 PM &ndash; 5:30 PM</td>
              <td data-label="Programme">Primary (P5 &ndash; P6)</td>
              <td data-label="Subjects">Mathematics, Science</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Day">Tuesday</td>
              <td data-label="Time">6:00 PM &ndash; 8:00 PM</td>
              <td data-label="Programme">Secondary (Sec 3 &ndash; 4/5)</td>
              <td data-label="Subjects">A Math, Chemistry, Physics</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Day">Wednesday</td>
              <td data-label="Time">4:00 PM &ndash; 5:30 PM</td>
              <td data-label="Programme">Primary (P3 &ndash; P6)</td>
              <td data-label="Subjects">English, Science</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Day">Wednesday</td>
              <td data-label="Time">6:30 PM &ndash; 8:30 PM</td>
              <td data-label="Programme">JC (JC1 &ndash; JC2)</td>
              <td data-label="Subjects">H2 Maths, H2 Physics</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Day">Thursday</td>
              <td data-label="Time">4:00 PM &ndash; 5:30 PM</td>
              <td data-label="Programme">Primary (P5 &ndash; P6)</td>
              <td data-label="Subjects">Mathematics, Higher Chinese</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Day">Thursday</td>
              <td data-label="Time">6:30 PM &ndash; 8:30 PM</td>
              <td data-label="Programme">JC (JC1 &ndash; JC2)</td>
              <td data-label="Subjects">H2 Chemistry, H2 Economics</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Day">Friday</td>
              <td data-label="Time">4:00 PM &ndash; 6:00 PM</td>
              <td data-label="Programme">Secondary (Sec 1 &ndash; 4/5)</td>
              <td data-label="Subjects">English, E Math</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Day">Friday</td>
              <td data-label="Time">6:30 PM &ndash; 8:30 PM</td>
              <td data-label="Programme">JC (JC1 &ndash; JC2)</td>
              <td data-label="Subjects">H1 General Paper</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Day">Saturday</td>
              <td data-label="Time">9:00 AM &ndash; 11:00 AM</td>
              <td data-label="Programme">Primary (P3 &ndash; P6)</td>
              <td data-label="Subjects">Mathematics, Science, English</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Day">Saturday</td>
